					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Sun Sep 19, 2004 11:12 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 9048<br /><b>Location:</b> NE Indiana, USA (NTSC)
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Banshaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Hmmm... I'm not sure what you mean by that since the msb of the PPUCTRL ($2000) is the NMI set bit.</div><br />Some of the <em>other</em> bits of PPUCTRL control the msb of the X and Y scroll position.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">How is it related to the scroll and why would you want to set it every time you scroll?  This is what I'm curious about right now.</div><br />Because when you set PPUCTRL, you have to set <em>all eight bits</em> of PPUCTRL. When you set the msb of the X and Y scroll position, you also set the NMI enable bit, and vice versa.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Just for other people that may read this thread, the constants used in this example are:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">PPUCTRL&nbsp; &nbsp;= $2000<br />PPUMASK&nbsp; &nbsp;= $2001<br />PPUSCROLL = $2005<br /><br />PPUCTRL_NMI = %10000000<br /></div></div><br />And I was talking about other bit fields in the register, like these:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">PPUCTRL_OBJ8X16&nbsp; = %00100000<br />PPUCTRL_BG1000&nbsp; &nbsp;= %00010000<br />PPUCTRL_OBJ1000&nbsp; = %00001000<br />PPUCTRL_VRAMDOWN = %00000100<br />PPUCTRL_Y240&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= %00000010<br />PPUCTRL_X256&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= %00000001<br /></div><br />When you write to one, you have to write to them all. If you do this:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda #PPUCTRL_NMI<br />sta PPUCTRL</div>
<br />you are setting all the other bits to 0. This is fine for games that don't scroll and only use the first 4 KiB of CHR and 8x8 pixel sprites.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

